original: Blidberg, Gösta, skeppsmäklare, Göteborg, f. 13/11/08 i Gbg av skeppsmäkl. David B. o. Augusta Pedersen. G. 34 m. Brita Kjellson. Barn: Claes f. 36, Krister 38. — Elev v. Gbgs h. samsk. o. Gbgs hand:inst. Prakt. 30, anst. h. F. W. Dahlström & Co. i Hamburg 31, h. Marcel Lebret i Paris 32, h. Galbraith, Pembroke & Co. Ltd i London, v. verkst. dir. i Blidberg, Metcalfe & Co. A-B i Gbg sed. 34. Led. av slyr. f. Västsv. Kylhus A-B o. A-B Götaberg.
translated: Blidberg, Gösta, ship broker, Gothenburg, born 13/11/08 in Gothenburg to ship broker David B. and Augusta Pedersen. Married in 1934 to Brita Kjellson, with children Claes born in 1936 and Krister born in 1938. He was a student at Gothenburg's Higher Latin School and Gothenburg's School of Business in 1930. He was employed by F. W. Dahlström & Co. in Hamburg in 1931, Marcel Lebret in Paris in 1932, and Galbraith, Pembroke & Co. Ltd in London before becoming the managing director of Blidberg, Metcalfe & Co. A-B in Gothenburg from 1934 onward. He was a member of the board of directors for Västsv. Kylhus A-B and A-B Götaberg.
